step.details:
Commit message format:
fix: upgrade {package} to {version} for CVE-{ID}

- Addresses CVE-{ID} in {package}
- Upgraded from {old-version} to {new-version}
- Concert recommendation: {recommendation-details}
- Resolves #{issue-number}

Push to origin remote
Use git push origin {branch-name}
Ensure branch is available for PR creation

Reference issue in PR description: Resolves #{issue-number}
Do NOT comment on the issue (PR link is automatic)
GitHub will auto-link PR to issue

Set pr_number output: {pr_number}
Set pr_branch output: fix/cve-{CVE-ID}-{package-name}
Set pr_url output: {full_pr_url}
These outputs trigger subsequent workflow steps

false_positive_update.payload:

{
  "status": "False positive",
  "comment": "Detailed justification from analysis. See GitHub issue link."
}
